The paper discusses the design and development of human-machine networks, which involves aspects of social interaction, human-computer interaction, cyber-physical systems, and system engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
